 istanbul, turkey (ap) _ three gunmen tossed two hand grenades into the garden of a military outpost during a roll-call in istanbul on friday after opening fire on a sentry, wounding 16 soldiers, reports said. leftist and kurdish guerrilla groups phoning several media organizations in istanbul claimed responsibility for the assault. the attack appeared to be the latest example of the collaboration between the leftist revolutionary people's salvation party-front and kurdish guerrillas, who are fighting for autonomy in turkey's southeast. the anatolia news agency said the attackers fled the scene by a car immediately after the attack at around 8 a.m. (0600 gmt) in gaziosmanpasa district, on the outskirts of istanbul. the injured, including an officer, were in stable condition, private ntv television said. the war between kurdish guerrillas and government forces in southeastern turkey has killed 37,000 people since 1984. (sh/vls) 